PROCESS INSTRUCTIONS: The assay is intended for the simultaneous qualitative detection and differentiation of the individual analytes HIV-1 p24 antigen, HIV-1 (groups M and O) antibodies, and HIV-2 antibodies. The assay may also be used as an aid in the diagnosis of infection with HIV-1 and/or HIV-2 in pediatric subjects as young as two years of age, and pregnant women.

COLLECTION INSTRUCTIONS:

, please contact the on-call Pulmonary physician.
PROCESS INSTRUCTIONS:
Patients with the following characteristics may not be able to generate enough sweat to accurately run this test: 

   - weight < 2 kg 

   - less than 36 weeks corrected gestational age 

   - younger than 48 hours old 

   - dehydrated 

   - on IV fluids in the past 12 hours 

If any of the above pertains to your patient, please consider delaying the testing or contact the on-call pulmonologist for approval.

PROCESS NAME: CHO LAB PROCESS INSTRUCTIONS - APTIMA SWAB
PROCESS INSTRUCTIONS: Call lab x3525 to obtain APTIMA Colletion Swab. OTHER SWAB TYPES ARE NOT ACCEPTABLE

Process instructions:  For eye, rectum, NP swabs, bronchial wash, and body fluid.   “Chlamydia & Gonorrhea Amplified DNA Urine” and “Chlamydia/Gonorrhea Amp DNA Vaginal Swab,” respectively, are superior for urine and vagi
nal specimens.



 Instructions for swabs:



1. Obtain Universal transport Media (UTM) with a FLOQSwab, available at the main lab.



2. In a sterile fashion, remove excess mucus.  



3. Use the FLOQSwab to collect epithelial cells from the affected mucosal surface.



4. Insert the swab into the UTM tube, snap off the shaft at the score line, and screw on the cap.  



5. IMPORTANT:  LABEL THE SPECIMEN WITH THE SOURCE (i.e. eye).



6. IMMEDIATELY transport to the lab on wet ice.



 Unacceptable specimens: Samples without source labeled, urine, wooden shaft or calcium alginate swabs, dry swabs, swabs in bacterial gel-based transport media, swabs in nucleic acid transport media, tissue in fixatives.

Patient must have fasted at least one hour prior to administering the breath test. Pranactin®-Citric contains a small amount of aspartame sweetener. Test may not be suitable for patients with phenylketonuria whose dietary phe
nylalanine should be restricted.



Follow collection instructions provided with the kit.

For the Diagnosis of Thalassemias and Hemoglobin Variants: 



Reflex testing - Hemoglobin Reflex testing performed at additional charge.



Cascade testing always start with Electrophoresis/CE/HPLC. If an abnormal HB is detected or if clinical data suggest a Hemoglobinopathy, appropriate reflex testing will be performed in order to provide a clinical interpretati
on. Multiple reflex test may be required. Reflex testing may include electrophoresis, solubility or molecular analysis of globin gene.
For patients anticoagulated with IV unfractionated heparin ONLY. NOT for patients on LMWH/Enoxaparin/Lovenox. Results are available 24/7.
